==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Seawant
<hw>Sea"want</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>The name used by the Algonquin Indians for
the shell beads which passed among the Indians as money.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <ex>Seawan</ex> was of two kinds; <stype>wampum</stype>,
white, and <stype>suckanhock</stype>, black or purple, -- the former
having half the value of the latter. Many writers, however, use the
terms <ex>seawan</ex> and <stype>wampum</stype> indiscriminately.</note>
<rj><au>Bartlett.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seawand</ent>⟦br⟧
